      "span_text": "The location of cord edema, however, is not suggestive of the location of fistula that may be located distant from the site of cord edema.  Following contrast administration, enhancement will be seen in the perimedullary veins and sometimes in the cord due to breakdown in the blood-spinal cord barrier."
